               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0030AP">ʿĀddaqāḥarsi Ṗarāqliṭos</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1900" notAfter="2000">20th cent.</origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>The names, Gabra Ḥǝywat and ʾAmata Mikāʾel,
                     are written in the supplication formulas at the beginning (<locus target="#5ra">5ra</locus>) and the end of the Vita (<locus target="#43rb">43rb</locus>,
                     43vb). Additionally, names of the members of his family are listed: Walda
                     Māryām (his father), Walatta Libānos (his mother) (<locus target="#5ra">5ra</locus>, 43rb, 43vb) and 10 names of his brothers and sisters (<locus target="#43rb">43rb</locus>). They were added later in a smaller script, in
                     the main hand.</provenance>
               </history>
